Toprak Group, a Turkish holding
company that lost control of many assets after the failure of
its lender Toprakbank, said it has paid off all its debt to the
Savings Deposit Insurance Fund.  The repayment means that 22 companies and 21 industrial
facilities belonging to the group will be returned to the
management of the Toprak family, according to an e-mailed
statement from the company.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Benjamin Harvey in Istanbul at 
